    String clazz = System.getProperty(DEFAULT_STORAGE_PROVIDER_PROPERTY);\\n        try {\\n            if (clazz != null) {\\n                instance = (StorageProvider) Class.forName(clazz).newInstance();\\n            }\\n        } catch (Exception e) {\\n        }\\n        if (instance == null) {\\n            StorageProvider backend = new TempFileStorageProvider();\\n            instance = new ThresholdStorageProvider(backend, 1024);\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    // for unit tests only\\n    static void reset() {\\n        instance = null;\\n        initialize();\\n    }\\n\\n}\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1777736344531}]}\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.apache.james:apache-mime4j-storage:0.8.13/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T15-40-10-425791Z.log:614:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_start\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 0, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"stop\", \"timestamp\": 1777736344544}}\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.apache.james:apache-mime4j-storage:0.8.13/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T15-40-10-425791Z.log:624:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Considering testing structure**\\n\\nI see that I need to focus on having a dedicated test under the tests directory, specifically in `src/test/java`. So, I'll inspect the existing tests to identify what I can build upon or replicate. It’s essential to ensure that the new tests fit seamlessly into the current structure. I want to make sure everything is organized and functioning well, which will help maintain the quality of the codebase!\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_01ebaa64272b6daa0169